                                <comments>
                            <comment id="16355679" author="jbonofre" created="Wed, 7 Feb 2018 16:41:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually, it&apos;s already merged as part of Kenn&apos;s last PR.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16355683" author="kenn" created="Wed, 7 Feb 2018 16:44:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Actually what I did was split the tests that didn&apos;t have stable names. This ticket is still valid - the tables created in each test method have different names otherwise they fail. It would be a little nicer if they dropped the table.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16355721" author="jbonofre" created="Wed, 7 Feb 2018 17:04:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yup, I meant that a first fix has been done. Now we need a better one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16356710" author="iemejia" created="Thu, 8 Feb 2018 09:27:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok just reassigned to Alexey given that he knows well HBase that should be an easy one. Only worry here is that deleting the tables will make the tests longer, but we&apos;ll see.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16356999" author="kenn" created="Thu, 8 Feb 2018 14:27:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yea, if it is a fake that will be dropped anyhow it might not matter to drop the tables one at a time. But maybe another way is to just make a pseudorandom suffix on the table name. The fanciest might be &lt;tt&gt;@Rule TemporaryHBaseTable&lt;/tt&gt;. Since it is fixed and pretty stable I set the priority low. We could leave it for a starter ticket if someone wanted to just get into the codebase.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16361056" author="aromanenko" created="Mon, 12 Feb 2018 16:51:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Disabling and truncating/deleting is quite expensive operation on mini-cluster. So I agree that using uniq table name would be better in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
